CATOS is not an outreach layer. It is the governance substrate of u-Kama.
The system does not treat communities as beneficiaries, labour pools, or compliance
actors. It treats them as the execution layer through which ecological continuity either
survives or collapses. Ecological truth is place-bound. Only those embedded in place
can carry uninterrupted obligation through drought cycles, political shifts, market
shocks, and generational change.
In technical terms, CATOS is the human constraint environment within which the
Ecological Boolean Gate can remain valid across stress windows.
If stewardship is outsourced, continuity fragments.
If continuity fragments, BGUs fail.
If BGUs fail, BDR does not advance.
The logic is simple.
